<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="143" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,759,1169]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,854,880]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Definition.</emphasis>
Terrestrial/aquatic life history, aquatic exotrophic larvae with keratinised feeding mouthparts, larvae&gt; 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
in maximum length, adults &lt;
<quantity box="[531,611,891,917]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="31.0">31 mm</quantity>
in maximum length, fourth toe length&gt; 
<quantity box="[1069,1126,891,917]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="7.0">7mm</quantity>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fletcher" authorityYear="1898" box="[1145,1222,891,917]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Crinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leai">
<emphasis box="[1145,1222,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">G. leai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName box="[1229,1377,891,917]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Geocrinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="victoriana">
<emphasis box="[1229,1377,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">G. victoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and&gt; 
<quantity box="[166,224,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="6.0">6mm</quantity>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1864" box="[239,337,927,953]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Pterophrynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[239,337,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">G. laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), testes mass&gt; 
<quantity box="[502,587,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-6" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" unit="g" value="0.001">0.001 g</quantity>
, egg compliment&gt;50; biphasic call, primarily autumn breeding.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,759,1169]" box="[199,1243,962,990]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,301,962,988]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Content.</emphasis>
Three species: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gunther)" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" box="[471,759,963,990]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Geocinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[471,642,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Geocinia laevis</emphasis>
(Günther)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fletcher)" baseAuthorityName="Fletcher" box="[770,927,963,990]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Crinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leai">
<emphasis box="[770,811,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">leai</emphasis>
(Fletcher)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boulenger)" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[985,1240,963,990]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Geocrinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="victoriana">
<emphasis box="[985,1098,963,988]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">victoriana</emphasis>
(Boulenger)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1085,998,1026]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,759,1169]" box="[199,1085,998,1026]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,349,998,1024]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Distribution.</emphasis>
Occurring in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[601,701,999,1025]" name="Australia" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Australia</collectingCountry>
(south-eastern and south-western).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="143" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,759,1169]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,1035,1061]" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1973" box="[542,653,1035,1061]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Geocrinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[542,653,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Geocrinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from Ancient Greek, a combination of the prefix γεω- (geô-) “earth” and verb κρῑνω (krînô) “to separate”. While no etymology was provided by Blake, it presumably means “earth 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tschudi" authorityYear="1838" box="[151,222,1107,1133]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Crinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,222,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Crinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, referring to the terrestrial egg deposition and larval development of the contained species relative to the aquatic life history of the morphologically similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tschudi" authorityYear="1838" box="[702,773,1143,1169]" class="Amphibia" family="Myobatrachidae" genus="Crinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="16" pageNumber="143" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[702,773,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="143">Crinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
